<subSubSection id="C37C5BEBFF92FFF0FF6203C83269FD33" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF92FFF0FF6203C830AEFE2D" blockId="5.[174,1233,413,462]" box="[174,980,440,462]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Troitsy”, on herbaceous plants, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE526EA7FF92FFF0FE1203C8311BFE2D" box="[478,609,440,462]" degrees="48" direction="north" minutes="32" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" precision="15" seconds="22" value="48.539444">48°32´22´´ N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE526EA7FF92FFF0FDA703C831A4FE2D" box="[619,734,440,462]" degrees="26" direction="east" minutes="25" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" precision="15" seconds="7" value="26.41861">26°25´7´´ E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<date id="FFD82EA0FF92FFF0FD2B03C83034FE2D" box="[743,846,440,462]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" value="2009-06-13">13.06.2009</date>
(Nazarenko).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF92FFF0FF2F03853269FD33" blockId="5.[174,1232,501,720]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Labrum slightly emarginate at the middle of apex. Central anterior epipharyngeal excision subrectangular as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF92FFF0FDDA00653103FDCD" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[534,633,532,558]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FDDA00653103FDCD" box="[534,633,532,558]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">H. miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Labral rods distinct, central depression between them suboval. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FEA4004432D3FDB6" box="[360,425,564,597]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Als 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FE43003732D3FDB6" attach="left" box="[399,425,583,597]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">1–3</subScript>
</emphasis>
approximately as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF92FFF0FD7A00453067FDAD" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[694,797,564,590]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miles">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FD7A00453067FDAD" box="[694,797,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">H. miles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FCE30045301AFDAD" box="[815,864,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">ams</emphasis>
short and directed obliquely forward. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FEEE00253226FD96" box="[290,348,597,629]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FE9800173226FD96" attach="left" box="[340,348,615,629]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
short, located together at the distal part of central cavity. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FB850025370CFD8C" box="[1097,1142,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Snp</emphasis>
placed near 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FF3D00053252FD76" box="[241,296,629,661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FEEC00F73252FD76" attach="left" box="[288,296,647,661]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
anterolaterally, consisted of 3-5 sensillae. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FC9F000530F7FD76" box="[851,909,629,661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FC4900F730F7FD76" attach="left" box="[901,909,647,661]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
more slender than 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FB5E000537B3FD76" box="[1170,1225,629,661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FB0D00F737B3FD76" attach="right" box="[1217,1225,647,661]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
, located in central depression. Epipharynx in distal part folded with transversal groups of teeth.
</paragraph>
